                    </div>
                    <span>The book is 1608 pages - 50% more than a James Michner book. It's published by Sam's. What more could it have against it?
<br />
<br />Yet it's a good book. If you're talking between .Net and COM it's got the information you need. Any chapter you open it to has good, readable information when you feel like browsing. It lies flat on a table when opened. What more could you ask for in a book?
<br />
<br />Definitely worth the price.</span>
                  
